There are court ladies from the Tang dynasty,

869
00:37:08,840 --> 00:37:11,680
and the Twelve Beauties from Dream of the Red Chamber.

870
00:37:12,200 --> 00:37:15,480
They all share one natural advantage,

871
00:37:15,480 --> 00:37:17,000
which is being widely recognized.

872
00:37:17,320 --> 00:37:18,800
And after my redesign,

873
00:37:19,040 --> 00:37:20,960
they've gained a brand-new quality,

874
00:37:20,960 --> 00:37:22,560
being ugly-cute.

875
00:37:22,920 --> 00:37:23,600
Uh, hey.

876
00:37:23,600 --> 00:37:25,680
Can we skip all that fluffy talk?

877
00:37:25,680 --> 00:37:28,600
Just explain it to everyone plainly.

878
00:37:28,600 --> 00:37:30,400
You're using these Xuan paper lumps

879
00:37:30,400 --> 00:37:32,800
to make these ugly-cute junk items.

880
00:37:33,000 --> 00:37:34,600
Can you guarantee anyone will buy them?

881
00:37:34,840 --> 00:37:36,080
Let me correct you first.

882
00:37:36,080 --> 00:37:37,520
I'm not selling junk.

883
00:37:37,520 --> 00:37:38,960
I'm selling emotional value.

884
00:37:38,960 --> 00:37:39,720
Of course, you wouldn't get it.

885
00:37:39,720 --> 00:37:40,840
I completely understand.

886
00:37:40,840 --> 00:37:41,960
After all, of those two words,

887
00:37:41,960 --> 00:37:43,080
you only fit one of them.

888
00:37:44,520 --> 00:37:45,120
Ugly-cute.

889
00:37:45,440 --> 00:37:47,600
It expresses young people's rebellious mindset.

890
00:37:48,320 --> 00:37:49,680
It's a whole new trendy way

891
00:37:49,680 --> 00:37:51,400
to show off individuality.

892
00:37:51,400 --> 00:37:54,400
It's a challenge to mainstream aesthetics.

893
00:37:55,600 --> 00:37:56,920
That's just empty talk.

894
00:37:57,040 --> 00:37:58,040
I don't know about you guys,

895
00:37:58,520 --> 00:38:00,600
but I really can't wrap my head around it.

896
00:38:01,160 --> 00:38:03,000
But to be fair,

897
00:38:03,040 --> 00:38:03,720
Young Master Xuan,

898
00:38:03,720 --> 00:38:05,640
that thing you mentioned before,

899
00:38:05,640 --> 00:38:07,520
the mini handmade papermaking series,

900
00:38:07,520 --> 00:38:09,040
I'm actually quite interested in that.

901
00:38:09,080 --> 00:38:10,000
But as for the rest,

902
00:38:10,000 --> 00:38:11,800
I really don't see the appeal.

903
00:38:15,640 --> 00:38:17,120
Personally, I'm very interested

904
00:38:17,120 --> 00:38:19,720
in Young Master Xuan's designs this time.

905
00:38:20,320 --> 00:38:21,440
I really like them too.

906
00:38:21,640 --> 00:38:23,560
Because none of us is perfect.

907
00:38:23,640 --> 00:38:25,080
I don't chase perfection.

908
00:38:25,080 --> 00:38:26,000
I'm just me.

909
00:38:27,000 --> 00:38:28,000
Young Master Xuan,

910
00:38:28,600 --> 00:38:31,320
what did you mean by "blind box" earlier?

911
00:38:31,320 --> 00:38:32,800
Mr. Huang, I wonder if you've ever

912
00:38:32,800 --> 00:38:34,040
collected trading cards before.

913
00:38:34,040 --> 00:38:36,600
Like the Water Margin character cards.

914
00:38:36,840 --> 00:38:37,560
When you buy them,

915
00:38:37,560 --> 00:38:39,360
you don't know which card you'll get.

916
00:38:39,360 --> 00:38:41,080
But you really want to collect

917
00:38:41,080 --> 00:38:42,040
every single character.

918
00:38:42,960 --> 00:38:43,840
I've done that.

919
00:38:44,080 --> 00:38:46,480
My classmates and I all fought over them.

920
00:38:46,680 --> 00:38:47,600
That kind of mindset

921
00:38:47,600 --> 00:38:50,400
is really about seeking emotional fulfillment.

922
00:38:51,560 --> 00:38:52,840
The appeal of blind boxes

923
00:38:52,840 --> 00:38:54,400
lies in their uncertainty

924
00:38:54,400 --> 00:38:55,920
and their scarcity.

925
00:38:56,560 --> 00:38:58,080
Through delayed gratification,

926
00:38:58,480 --> 00:39:01,920
they give people a huge emotional thrill.

927
00:39:02,160 --> 00:39:04,800
And winners feel a greater sense of achievement.

928
00:39:05,320 --> 00:39:05,880
What?

929
00:39:05,880 --> 00:39:07,680
Astro Boy?

930
00:39:07,800 --> 00:39:09,360
Isn't that just for little kids?

931
00:39:09,960 --> 00:39:12,040
Mr. Zhang, you're so mature.

932
00:39:12,520 --> 00:39:14,920
You can't even let someone finish talking.

933
00:39:19,720 --> 00:39:20,720
Are you done yet?

934
00:39:24,280 --> 00:39:25,320
Then let me say a few words.

935
00:39:26,520 --> 00:39:27,320
Personally,

936
00:39:27,320 --> 00:39:28,520
I'm very interested in

937
00:39:28,520 --> 00:39:29,880
Young Master Xuan's design concept

938
00:39:29,880 --> 00:39:31,280
this time around.

939
00:39:32,120 --> 00:39:33,560
His brand-new design philosophy

940
00:39:33,560 --> 00:39:35,880
gives our company's future products

941
00:39:35,880 --> 00:39:38,400
a very unique direction.

942
00:39:38,400 --> 00:39:39,720
And what he just mentioned,

943
00:39:39,720 --> 00:39:41,360
the blind box sales model,

944
00:39:41,400 --> 00:39:43,000
also offers us

945
00:39:43,000 --> 00:39:44,160
a very special suggestion.

946
00:39:44,600 --> 00:39:45,440
For our Dayazhai,

947
00:39:45,440 --> 00:39:47,040
all of this

948
00:39:47,040 --> 00:39:49,000
would be a brand-new venture.

949
00:39:49,280 --> 00:39:51,440
I'm someone who welcomes challenges.

950
00:39:51,440 --> 00:39:52,800
What does everyone else think?

951
00:39:57,880 --> 00:39:58,520
Everyone,

952
00:39:59,040 --> 00:40:01,520
let me kick things off here.

953
00:40:01,920 --> 00:40:03,520
First off, I'm against it.

954
00:40:04,000 --> 00:40:05,400
I want to remind everyone,

955
00:40:05,600 --> 00:40:07,920
don't just play the nice guy.

956
00:40:08,040 --> 00:40:10,680
You must make your stance clear.

957
00:40:10,680 --> 00:40:12,280
Especially to the Chairman.

958
00:40:16,040 --> 00:40:18,840
If you're so eager to report to him,

959
00:40:19,000 --> 00:40:20,320
you can leave right now.

960
00:40:20,320 --> 00:40:21,640
No, what's that supposed to mean?

961
00:40:21,640 --> 00:40:24,000
Why the snide tone?

962
00:40:24,000 --> 00:40:26,120
Can't anyone speak up in a meeting?

963
00:40:26,360 --> 00:40:28,080
As for young Master Xuan's design,

964
00:40:28,080 --> 00:40:29,360
personally, I think

965
00:40:29,400 --> 00:40:31,200
it's worth considering a try.

966
00:40:31,840 --> 00:40:32,920
What I'm most worried about

967
00:40:32,920 --> 00:40:35,200
is the marketing strategy and funding.

968
00:40:35,560 --> 00:40:38,280
Take these Twelve Beauties of Jinling,

969
00:40:38,680 --> 00:40:40,600
the first six released

970
00:40:40,600 --> 00:40:42,880
will definitely be low-priced to grab the market.

971
00:40:43,080 --> 00:40:43,920
By doing this,

972
00:40:44,160 --> 00:40:47,000
we want to cultivate a customer base

973
00:40:47,040 --> 00:40:48,920
that gets into the habit

974
00:40:48,920 --> 00:40:50,000
of buying blind boxes.

975
00:40:50,520 --> 00:40:51,680
I get it now.

976
00:40:51,920 --> 00:40:53,640
For example, someone

977
00:40:53,640 --> 00:40:55,560
who's already bought these six cheap ones,

978
00:40:55,560 --> 00:40:57,840
if they want to collect the other six,

979
00:40:57,880 --> 00:40:59,080
the price will go up, right?

980
00:40:59,560 --> 00:41:01,120
So the first six released

981
00:41:01,120 --> 00:41:01,920
are basically what?

982
00:41:01,920 --> 00:41:03,320
Losing money to build buzz.

983
00:41:03,920 --> 00:41:05,320
So for this investment,

984
00:41:05,320 --> 00:41:06,480
roughly how much will it be?

985
00:41:08,520 --> 00:41:10,400
The capital needed for this

986
00:41:10,400 --> 00:41:12,320
I estimate at 8 to 10 million.

987
00:41:13,640 --> 00:41:15,120
No way.

988
00:41:15,840 --> 00:41:16,880
What do you mean, no way?

989
00:41:17,000 --> 00:41:18,440
Is investing your call to make?

990
00:41:18,440 --> 00:41:20,160
Well, it's not your call either.

991
00:41:20,880 --> 00:41:21,640
Fine, everyone.

992
00:41:21,640 --> 00:41:23,040
I've said all I need to say.

993
00:41:23,400 --> 00:41:24,880
You can keep discussing.

994
00:41:25,480 --> 00:41:26,280
Xuan Yan,

995
00:41:27,360 --> 00:41:29,000
if you end up not using this,

996
00:41:29,000 --> 00:41:29,720
send it back to me.

997
00:41:33,120 --> 00:41:34,680
Manager Huang, see him out.

998
00:41:35,880 --> 00:41:36,800
I think

999
00:41:36,840 --> 00:41:38,000
the investment risk is significant.

1000
00:41:38,000 --> 00:41:39,120
I suggest the company

1001
00:41:39,120 --> 00:41:40,000
consider carefully.

1002
00:41:40,440 --> 00:41:41,200
That's all from me.

1003
00:41:42,360 --> 00:41:43,880
He's hit the nail on the head.

1004
00:41:45,160 --> 00:41:47,000
Just now, young Master Xuan

1005
00:41:47,000 --> 00:41:48,520
just flapped his lips.

1006
00:41:49,000 --> 00:41:50,400
It's easy to say,

1007
00:41:50,600 --> 00:41:51,880
but in the end,

1008
00:41:52,800 --> 00:41:54,480
huge investments,

1009
00:41:54,840 --> 00:41:56,280
bearing enormous pressure,

1010
00:41:56,280 --> 00:41:57,960
that all falls on us.

1011
00:41:57,960 --> 00:41:59,720
He just gets to collect the returns.

1012
00:42:00,320 --> 00:42:01,120
Isn't that right?

1013
00:42:01,360 --> 00:42:03,000
And who can guarantee

1014
00:42:03,080 --> 00:42:03,960
that after pouring in all this money,

1015
00:42:03,960 --> 00:42:05,600
there's bound to be a return?

1016
00:42:06,040 --> 00:42:06,520
So,

1017
00:42:06,520 --> 00:42:07,600
I'll say it once more,

1018
00:42:08,120 --> 00:42:11,320
all major company decisions

1019
00:42:11,680 --> 00:42:13,920
must be approved by the Chairman.

1020
00:42:14,280 --> 00:42:15,800
I'll report to the Chairman.

1021
00:42:15,800 --> 00:42:16,320
Wonderful.

1022
00:42:16,320 --> 00:42:17,400
After you've reported,

1023
00:42:17,400 --> 00:42:19,000
we'll decide.

1024
00:42:19,000 --> 00:42:19,520
Meeting adjourned.

1025
00:42:32,560 --> 00:42:33,080
President Xiao.

1026
00:42:34,360 --> 00:42:34,840
What is it?

1027
00:42:34,840 --> 00:42:35,400
Is it cute?

1028
00:42:35,400 --> 00:42:36,440
Yes, cute, cute, cute.

1029
00:42:36,440 --> 00:42:38,840
Didn't you say young people love these?

1030
00:42:38,840 --> 00:42:41,440
If young people like it, that's great.

1031
00:42:42,280 --> 00:42:44,320
Xuan Yan, look at the time.

1032
00:42:44,320 --> 00:42:45,400
Why isn't Xin Ran here yet?

1033
00:42:45,720 --> 00:42:48,920
No wonder President Xiao seems so distracted.

1034
00:42:48,920 --> 00:42:51,200
Turns out he's pining for Sister Xin.

1035
00:42:51,200 --> 00:42:51,920
Oh, come on.

1036
00:42:54,360 --> 00:42:56,600
Xin Ran probably can't make it.

1037
00:42:57,520 --> 00:42:58,280
Why not?
